                    <span>The book brings back historically those features that are essential in any strategy for most activities, altgough is focused in war. Basic reading for bussines.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Excellent & Easy reading</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>22</span>
                      /
                      <span>24</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-08-16</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>"The Making of Strategy" examines the strategy-making processes through the cultural, social, political, organisational and historical ( not just the military ) lenses, starting from the Peloponnesian Wars to the Nuclear Age. The book is also excellent in inrtoducing the concept of Weltanschauung; how a nation's strategic choices are often products of its strategic culture. This helps the reader to understand that despite advances in military technologies; why most wars are fought the way they are fought. Very easy reading and excellent book on the little known process of how strategy is often made.</span>
                  
              
